ABUJA – A group under the aegies of the North American Movement To Engage Amaechi (NAMEAMAECHI) has launched a website in the faraway city of Virginia, the USA for the Transportation Minister Chibuike Amaechi’s Presidential bid. Publishers / Founders of the website, Dr. Ogu Emejuru, a Fellow of the American Academy of Pediatrics and Co-founder, Prof. Bisi Oladipupo, a Professor of Engineering disclosed that the idea is aimed at ensuring robust publicity for the Transportation Minister who is a frontline aspirant for the 2023 Presidential election. The duo called on the people of Nigeria to support the Presidential ambition of Amaechi, whom they described as a goal-getter and development champion. -Advertisement- They also enjoined the general public to visit the website www.nameamaechi.com to have first-hand information on the achievements and activities of the Presidential hopeful.